* ============================================================
*  TABLE-BUFFER WAL — PHASE A PROOF (durable redo log on COMMIT/ROLLBACK)
*
*  Status:  CANDIDATE / REVIEW_BEFORE_EXECUTION.
*  Safety:  MUTATING, but only on a throwaway table (WALDEMO) ERASEd at the end.
*  Purpose: Prove that with TABLE BUFFER ON PERSISTENT (RAM+JOURNAL), buffered
*           REPLACEs are written to a durable .tbj redo log, COMMIT applies them
*           (marker fsync BEFORE apply, log removed after), and ROLLBACK discards.
*           The observable checks here are the COMMIT-applies / ROLLBACK-discards
*           behavior; the .tbj file itself is created next to the run dir and
*           removed on commit/rollback (inspect it by adding a QUIT before COMMIT).
*
*  RUN (host):
*    powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\dottalkpp\data\scripts\pinocchio\run_wal_phaseA_proof_teed.ps1
* ============================================================
SET ECHO OFF
SET TIMER ON
SET TALK ON

ECHO === P0. build throwaway x64 table WALDEMO with two rows ===
CREATE X64 WALDEMO (ID N(4), NAME C(20))
APPEND
REPLACE ID WITH "1"
REPLACE NAME WITH "Alpha"
APPEND
REPLACE ID WITH "2"
REPLACE NAME WITH "Beta"
COUNT

ECHO === P1. enable persistent (RAM+JOURNAL) table buffering ===
TABLE BUFFER ON PERSISTENT
TABLE BUFFER STATUS

ECHO === P2. buffered + logged REPLACE on recno 1 (NAME -> Alpha2), not yet applied ===
GO 1
REPLACE NAME WITH "Alpha2"

ECHO === P3. COMMIT: WAL marker fsynced before apply, then log removed ===
COMMIT
GO 1
ECHO --- recno 1 NAME should now be Alpha2 (committed) ---
DISPLAY

ECHO === P4. buffered REPLACE on recno 2 (NAME -> RolledBk) then ROLLBACK ===
GO 2
REPLACE NAME WITH "RolledBk"
ROLLBACK
GO 2
ECHO --- recno 2 NAME should still be Beta (rolled back) ---
DISPLAY

ECHO === P5. HISTORY MODE: multiple retained edits per field are kept + logged ===
TABLE BUFFER HISTORY ON
TABLE BUFFER STATUS
GO 1
REPLACE NAME WITH "Edit1"
REPLACE NAME WITH "Edit2"
REPLACE NAME WITH "Edit3"
ECHO --- DUMP: recno 1 should show THREE retained NAME edits (priorities 1,2,3), NOT folded ---
ECHO --- the .tbj log likewise has 3 U records: "U 1 1 H NAME:..", "U 1 2 H ..", "U 1 3 H .." ---
TABLE BUFFER DUMP
ECHO --- COMMIT applies the highest-priority value (Edit3); the log retained all three ---
COMMIT
GO 1
DISPLAY
TABLE BUFFER HISTORY OFF

ECHO === P6. cleanup: disable buffer, close, erase ===
TABLE BUFFER OFF
CLOSE
ERASE TABLE WALDEMO CONFIRM

ECHO ============================================================
ECHO WAL PHASE A PROOF COMPLETE. Confirm:
ECHO   P3: recno 1 NAME = Alpha2 (COMMIT applied the buffered+logged change).
ECHO   P4: recno 2 NAME = Beta   (ROLLBACK discarded the buffered change).
ECHO   P5: DUMP showed 3 retained NAME edits for recno 1 (history mode preserved);
ECHO       after COMMIT recno 1 NAME = Edit3 (highest priority). Log kept all 3.
ECHO   No crash under the new durable-log path; RAM+JOURNAL mode active in STATUS.
ECHO   (A .tbj redo log is written under the run dir and removed on commit/rollback.)
ECHO ============================================================
